==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fire beetle
<hw>Fire" bee`tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A very
brilliantly luminous beetle (<spn>Pyrophorus noctilucus</spn>), one of
the elaters, found in Central and South America; -- called also
<altname>cucujo</altname>. The name is also applied to other species.
See <er>Firefly</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firebird</ent>⟦br⟧
